On Sun, Jan 31, 1999 at 10:21:05AM +0100, ralf@uni-koblenz.de wrote:
> The magic number which I cannot remember ever having been posted is the
> time it takes to fsck such a partition.
without _too_ much data - 400GB will fsck in less than a minute. With
lots of large (1GB+) files, it takes somewhat longer...
With plenty of small files, it probably won't finish this
millenium.
-cw
(btw -- tested with big black SGI disk vault system, which presumably
does fancy stuff internally to speek things up)
